Reward!!! Volkswagen Syncro 16"stolen
(PICTURE: http://computer.freepage.de/syncro16/vw_syncro_rot.jpg ) VOLKSWAGEN Multivan Syncro 16 ", Red,
Turbo-Diesel engine (identification letter JX, exchange engine)
Licence plate B-CD 1808
Chassisnumber WV2ZZZ25ZMG011887
In the time between 24.10.2002, 15:00 h to 25,10,2002, 17:45 h in
Berlin in the Woertherstrasse in front of the copying shop on the corner Rykestrasse stolen. The vehicle has a ramming protection
guard (bullbar) in front (make Budich or something like that) with inserted rope winch, where the actually the spare wheel well is,
On the front sheet metal, the decals "Red star" and "syncro". And on the front doors the decals "4WD".

Further accessories mounted: Sliding window, Darkened tinted windows with black framework, widening screens to the tail lamps,
Seikel feathers/springs and tyres BFGoodrich all terrain 225/75 R16, Differential lock in front and rear, however front not yet
attached,  switch not mounted yet.
The car comes with an interior from a xxx star/LLE and the spare wheel is mounted onto the seat stand behind the passenger seat.
On the spare wheel a small high-grade steel sink had been provisionally fastened, the two (jerry)cans for it stood beside it. Radio
with cassette and CD-changer, make Blaupunkt "Carolina DJ52", only three months old.

People who has sighted this vehicle or if someone was trying to sell the vehicle to you (Incl. parts of it) please report to me or
each police station in Germany.
For reports, leading to the locating of the vehicle and returning to the rightfull owner or even better also to the capture of the
thieves will be rewarded with a fee of EURO 500,-- !!!
C Diergardt
Tel. (Germany) 030-25700775
email: c.di(-at-)berlin.de



